<p>I am pretty new in Spring and I have the following problem with a Spring MVC application.</p>  <p>Into an old Spring MVC project that use <strong>thymeleaf</strong> as view technology I did something like this to pass an object initialized with the value inserted in the form:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;form id="gestioneImpegno" th:object="${gestioneImpegno}" action="salvaImpegno" th:action="@{/Pagamenti/stampa}" method="get" class="form-horizontal"&gt;     .....................................................................     .....................................................................     .....................................................................     &lt;tr&gt;         &lt;td align="center" &gt;&lt;input type="checkbox" th:field="*{listaBeneficiariSelezionati}" th:value="|${beneficiario.tsc1004Progetto.codCup}|" /&gt;     &lt;/tr&gt;     .....................................................................     .....................................................................     ..................................................................... &lt;/form&gt; </code></pre>  <p>In the specific case when the user click on the checkbobox related to a table row and the value of a model object field (represented by <strong>th:value="|${beneficiario.tsc1004Progetto.codCup}|"</strong>) it is putted into the list represented by <strong>th:field="*{listaBeneficiariSelezionati}"</strong> and that is specified in the form definition by <strong>th:object="${gestioneImpegno}"</strong></p>  <p>Ok it works.</p>  <p>The problem is that now I am working on another Spring MVC project that use standard JSP page.</p>  <p>I have to do something like this using JSP.</p>  <p>So in this new project I have something like this:</p>  <pre><code>&lt;form id="validazioneForm" action="validaProgettiChecked"&gt;                                 th:action="@{/Pagamenti/stampa}" method="get" class="form-horizontal"&gt;     &lt;table id="tabellaConsultazione" class="display table table-striped table-bordered sortable" style="width: 100%;"&gt;         &lt;thead&gt;             &lt;tr&gt;                 &lt;th&gt;&lt;input name="select_all" value="1" type="checkbox"&gt;&lt;/th&gt;                 &lt;th&gt;Codice meccanografico attuale&lt;/th&gt;                 &lt;th&gt;Codice meccanografico iniziale&lt;/th&gt;             &lt;/tr&gt;         &lt;/thead&gt;         &lt;tbody&gt;             &lt;c:forEach items="${listaProgetti.lista}" var="progetto" varStatus="itemProgetto"&gt;                 &lt;tr&gt;                     &lt;td&gt;&lt;input type="checkbox"&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                     &lt;td&gt;&lt;a onClick="modalDettaglioScuola('&lt;c:out value="${progetto.tws1002AnagistscolAtt.id.codScuUt}" /&gt;')"&gt;&lt;c:out value="${progetto.tws1002AnagistscolAtt.id.codScuUt}" /&gt;&lt;/a&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                     &lt;td&gt;&lt;c:out value="${progetto.codMecIniPro}" /&gt;&lt;/td&gt;                 &lt;/tr&gt;             &lt;/c:forEach&gt;         &lt;/tbody&gt;     &lt;/table&gt; &lt;/form&gt; </code></pre>  <p>So what I need to do is that when the user click on a checkbox the value of the <strong>progetto.prgPro</strong> field is putted into a list defined on the form (as done by the <strong>th:object="${gestioneImpegno}"</strong> in the old thymeleaf page).</p>  <p>How can I do something like this using JSP?</p>